abstract: SUBSIDENCE OF THE PANIC. - There is one good thing about a panic, and especially a financial panic ; from the very nature of the phenomenon it cannot last long. The financial panic of the present season reached its culminating point last week, and the subsidence is now very perceptibly felt.

abstract: To the Editor of the New-York Times: SIR: I see in your paper of Saturday an article on life-preservers. abstract: To the Editor of the New - York Times: I was very glad to see your article in Saturday's paper upon railway management, and I quite agree with you in the opinion that the time has now come for a through reformation.
